msgid "// x is now type u32 in Edition 2024\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2024/intoiterator-box-slice.md:52
msgid "Migration"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2024/intoiterator-box-slice.md:54
msgid ""
"The [`boxed_slice_into_iter`](../../rustc/lints/listing/warn-by-default."
"html#boxed-slice-into-iter) lint will automatically modify any calls to `."
"into_iter()` on boxed slices to call `.iter()` instead to retain the old "
"behavior of yielding references. This lint is part of the `rust-2024-"
"compatibility` lint group, which will automatically be applied when running "
"`cargo fix --edition`. To migrate your code to be Rust 2024 Edition "
"compatible, run:"
msgstr ""

